        "cooked": "<p>I send a lot of pictures where I just need to point out basic details in a very straightfoward way. For example, if I took a sent a picture of where I wanted a visitor to park, I might use an arrow to indicate which parking spot is mine. If thereâ€™s an important detail in a busy picture with many distractions, an arrow is just the thing! Thereâ€™s lots more examples but it gives rise to my idea for simple annotation tools in the image editor.</p>\n<p>For example:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Arrows - ideally with settable colours. Once you get used to using them youâ€™d not believe how much can be solved by a simple red arrow pointing something out. Ideally settable thickness too (like the pen tool already has). Flexible, like a typical image editorâ€™s line tool (i.e. I can draw it any length, from any point to any point on the image)</li>\n<li>Circles and Squares</li>\n<li>You can go further, like highlights, callouts (text boxes with arrows attached) but you get the idea - the above 3 are the most useful.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>These could compliment the text tool already present. I suggest a simple, plain arrow tool (essentially a line tool but with an arrow end) that produces an end result similar to this <a href=\"https://iconmonstr.com/arrow-left-lined-svg/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">arrow illustration from iconmonstr</a>:</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/6/a/6a52dc2410431be9513779bd24e8275db224adce.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/6a52dc2410431be9513779bd24e8275db224adce\" title=\"iconmonstr-arrow-left-lined-240(1)\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/6/a/6a52dc2410431be9513779bd24e8275db224adce.png\" alt=\"iconmonstr-arrow-left-lined-240(1)\" data-base62-sha1=\"faA8A9PW0wILkUqxdMLuNZf2Inc\" width=\"240\" height=\"240\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">iconmonstr-arrow-left-lined-240(1)</span><span class=\"informations\">240Ã—240 567 Bytes</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>",
